Liverpool just did enough to pick up three points against West Ham as David Moyes’ side spurned chances to equalise at Anfield. Liverpool came close to taking the lead inside the first minute. Mohamed Salah advanced towards goal but his shot was saved by Lukasz Fabianski. The hosts did eventually go ahead in the 27th minute. This came as Sadio Mane converted Trent Alexander-Arnold’s low cross from close range. Brandon Williams Angrily Grabs Christian Eriksen But Then Hugs… Newcastle Battle Tottenham In Race To Zaniolo West Ham had their fair share of opportunities at Anfield and had they not been wasteful they may have earned themselves a point. Liverpool hung on though to pick up a much-needed three points. They are now three points behind Man City ahead of the Manchester derby on Sunday afternoon.